{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:17:17.209395+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 8d71d8125861b72e1904d79cc9bbad3ab2ce83d4)", "id": "lc_056c2aa0-81bb-44d1-9b6a-b24950c28260"}, {"type": "text", "text": "FROM python:3.10-slim as base\n\n# Create a non-root user to run the app with.\nRUN groupadd --gid 1000 user &&  adduser --disabled-password --gecos '' --uid 1000 --gid 1000 user\nUSER user\n\nWORKDIR /home/user/app\n\n# Install Poetry.\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache pip install --user poetry==1.4.2\nENV \\\n    PATH=\"/home/user/.local/bin:/home/user/app/.venv/bin:${PATH}\" \\\n    PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 \\\n    POETRY_NO_INTERACTION=1 \\\n    POETRY_VIRTUALENVS_IN_PROJECT=true\n\nCOPY --chown=user:user ./pyproject.toml ./poetry.lock ./alembic.ini ./\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache poetry install\n\nFROM base as dev\n\nCOPY --chown=user:user ./api api\n\nCMD [\"uvicorn\", \"api.main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"5000\", \"--reload\"]\n\n\nFROM base as test\n\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends git-core\nUSER user\n\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache poetry install --with dev\n\n# For running pre-commit\nCOPY --chown=user:user ./.git .git\nCOPY --chown=user:user ./.pre-commit-config.yaml .pre-commit-config.yaml\n\nRUN mkdir /home/user/.mypy_cache && chown -R user:user /home/user/.mypy_cache\nRUN pre-commit install --install-hooks\n\nCOPY --chown=user:user ./api api\n\n# Default target.\nFROM dev\n", "id": "lc_dd3556f4-a3c0-409f-9afd-dac5a2513f42"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "6c0c3a99-a4d3-4555-9e88-778c57b8eb09", "tool_call_id": "call_73069e0eedb646569e146e05", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:17:31.131959+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here's how to start the FastAPI project locally with Docker and apply database migrations:\n\n## Starting the FastAPI Project with Docker\n\n1. **Clone the repository** and navigate to the project directory:\n   ```sh\n   git clone https://github.com/Donnype/fastapi-template.git\n   cd fastapi-template\n   ```\n\n2. **Start the application** using the Make command:\n   ```sh\n   make up\n   ```\n   This runs `docker compose up -d --build api`, which:\n   - Builds the API container from `api/Dockerfile`\n   - Starts a PostgreSQL database container (postgres:14.5)\n   - Mounts the local `./api` directory for live code reloading\n   - Sets the database connection string: `postgresql://postgres:test@db:5432/postgres`\n\n3. **Access the API** at: `http://localhost:5000/docs`\n\n## Applying Database Migrations\n\nTo apply database migrations using Alembic:\n\n```sh\nmake migrate\n```\n\nThis runs `docker compose run --rm api alembic upgrade head`, which:\n- Executes all pending Alembic migrations\n- Updates the database schema to the latest version\n\n### Additional Migration Commands\n\nFrom the Makefile, you can also:\n- **Generate new migrations**: `make migrations m=\"{message}\" revid=\"{revid}\"`\n- **Downgrade one migration**: `make downgrade`\n\n### Docker Architecture\n\nThe `docker-compose.yml` defines two services:\n- **api**: FastAPI application (port 5000) with live code reloading\n- **db**: PostgreSQL 14.5 database (port 5432) with persistent data volume\n\nThe API container uses Poetry for dependency management and includes Alembic for database migrations, with the migration scripts located in `api/migrations/`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 738, "prompt_tokens": 10325, "total_tokens": 11063, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_